<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="210" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,1191,2015]" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,382,1295,1321]" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">Measurements.</emphasis>
Total length: 14.6–14.7; head length: 1.4–1.5; head width: 2.9–3.0; pronotal width: 8.4–8.7; abdominal width: 7.2–7.9; length of antennal segments. I: 0.9–0.9; II: 1.6–1.7; III: 1.4–1.4; IV: 4.0–4.4; V: 4.5–0.0; interocular distance: 1.2–1.7; scutellum length: 6.7–6.9; scutellum width: 4.9–5.0; pronotal length: 2.7–2.8.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="210" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,1191,2015]" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1399,1425]" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Anterolateral margin of pronotum with solid black stripe reaching all its extension. Anterolateral margin with some brown punctures dorsally. Cicatrices with dark brown punctures delimiting anterior sulci (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[241,1344,194,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-20@31.[226,1361,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 20. Dorsal and ventral view. H. runcinatus sp. n. A–B; H. similis sp. n. C–D; H. trilobulatus sp. n. E–F; H. unguiculatus sp. n. G–H; H. ventrotuberculatus sp. n. I–J (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777100" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777100/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">Fig. 20E</figureCitation>
). Body ventrally with brown stripes (
<figureCitation box="[623,724,1468,1495]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[241,1344,194,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-20@31.[226,1361,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 20. Dorsal and ventral view. H. runcinatus sp. n. A–B; H. similis sp. n. C–D; H. trilobulatus sp. n. E–F; H. unguiculatus sp. n. G–H; H. ventrotuberculatus sp. n. I–J (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777100" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777100/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">Fig. 20F</figureCitation>
). Male (
<figureCitation box="[818,959,1468,1495]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[236,1344,186,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-20@25.[219,1368,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 15. Hypoxys trilobulatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777090/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">Fig. 15A–D</figureCitation>
). Pygophore with dorsal rim sinuous (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[236,1344,186,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-20@25.[219,1368,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 15. Hypoxys trilobulatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777090/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">Fig. 15A</figureCitation>
). Superior process of genital cup with distal part rounded, thick and medially concave, proximal part widely bifid; process next to dorsal rim; visible in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[800,940,1538,1565]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[236,1344,186,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-20@25.[219,1368,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 15. Hypoxys trilobulatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777090/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">Fig. 15A–C</figureCitation>
). Paramere with an elongated lobe dorsally directed, apex rounded; posterior lobe short and triangular; inner low carina splitting distally finishing at anterior and posterior apices (
<figureCitation box="[400,538,1607,1634]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[236,1344,186,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-20@25.[219,1368,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 15. Hypoxys trilobulatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777090/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">Fig. 15B–C</figureCitation>
). Proctiger with dorsal tufts of short setae separated by sparsely setose ridge; posterior face pentagonal (
<figureCitation box="[453,592,1642,1669]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[236,1344,186,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-20@25.[219,1368,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 15. Hypoxys trilobulatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777090/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">Fig. 15A–C</figureCitation>
). Ventral rim with expansions acuminated, yellow, clearly surpassing level of posterolateral angles in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[613,719,1676,1703]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[236,1344,186,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-20@25.[219,1368,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 15. Hypoxys trilobulatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777090/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">Fig. 15D</figureCitation>
). Female (
<figureCitation box="[840,943,1676,1703]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[236,1344,186,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-20@25.[219,1368,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 15. Hypoxys trilobulatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777090/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">Fig. 15E</figureCitation>
). Valvifers 8 with posterior margin sinuous and distally truncate over valvifers 9; lateral margin depressed; inner margin dark and deeply excavated, U-shaped. Valvulae 8 widely exposed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="210" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,1191,2015]" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1780,1806]" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">Comments.</emphasis>
The paramere of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[542,709,1780,1806]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trilobulatus">
<emphasis box="[542,709,1780,1806]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">H. trilobulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1907" box="[839,961,1780,1806]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dolosus">
<emphasis box="[839,961,1780,1806]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">H. dolosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1907" box="[977,1133,1780,1806]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eburatulus">
<emphasis box="[977,1133,1780,1806]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">H. eburatulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[1198,1338,1780,1806]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flexuosus">
<emphasis box="[1198,1338,1780,1806]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">H. flexuosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because anterior lobe is developed and directed dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[690,801,1815,1842]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[236,1344,186,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-20@25.[219,1368,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 15. Hypoxys trilobulatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777090/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">Figs. 15B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[812,847,1815,1841]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[229,1360,193,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-23@14.[214,1373,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Hypoxys flexuosus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777076" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777076/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">8B</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Nunes, B. M. &amp; Campos, L. D. &amp; Mendonca, M. T. S. &amp; Cunha, E. V. P. &amp; Fernandes, J. A. M." box="[858,1055,1815,1842]" pageId="23" pageNumber="210" pagination="401 - 441" refId="ref18209" refString="Nunes, B. M., Campos, L. D., Mendonca, M. T. S., Cunha, E. V. P. &amp; Fernandes, J. A. M. (2020) Revision of Hypoxys Amyot &amp; Serville, 1843 stat. rest. (Heteroptera Pentatomidae). Zootaxa, 4742 (3), 401 - 441. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4742.3.1" type="journal article" year="2020">
Nunes 
<emphasis box="[935,983,1815,1841]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">et al</emphasis>
. 2020
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1065,1160,1815,1841]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1915,1939]" captionTargetBox="[161,1417,544,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-158@8.[151,1436,525,1892]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Hypoxys crassimarginatum sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777068" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777068/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">Figs. 4B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1171,1207,1815,1842]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[237,1347,191,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-23@10.[219,1367,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Hypoxys cristatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777070" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777070/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">5B</figureCitation>
). But 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[1272,1437,1815,1841]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trilobulatus">
<emphasis box="[1272,1437,1815,1841]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">H. trilobulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has trilobulate superior process of the genital cup (without lobes in the others). Also, posterior lobe of the paramere is slightly developed and triangular in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[585,751,1884,1910]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trilobulatus">
<emphasis box="[585,751,1884,1910]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">H. trilobulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(rounded and barely developed in the others). The female of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[151,318,1919,1945]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trilobulatus">
<emphasis box="[151,318,1919,1945]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">H. trilobulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the excavation of inner margins of valvifers 8 deep and cup-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[1154,1256,1919,1946]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[236,1344,186,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-20@25.[219,1368,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 15. Hypoxys trilobulatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777090/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">Fig. 15E</figureCitation>
), meanwhile 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1907" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dolosus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">H. dolosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1907" box="[293,449,1954,1980]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eburatulus">
<emphasis box="[293,449,1954,1980]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">H. eburatulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a V-shaped excavation (
<bibRefCitation author="Nunes, B. M. &amp; Campos, L. D. &amp; Mendonca, M. T. S. &amp; Cunha, E. V. P. &amp; Fernandes, J. A. M." box="[788,993,1954,1980]" pageId="23" pageNumber="210" pagination="401 - 441" refId="ref18209" refString="Nunes, B. M., Campos, L. D., Mendonca, M. T. S., Cunha, E. V. P. &amp; Fernandes, J. A. M. (2020) Revision of Hypoxys Amyot &amp; Serville, 1843 stat. rest. (Heteroptera Pentatomidae). Zootaxa, 4742 (3), 401 - 441. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4742.3.1" type="journal article" year="2020">
Nunes 
<emphasis box="[869,919,1954,1980]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">et al</emphasis>
. 2020
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1005,1106,1954,1980]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1915,1939]" captionTargetBox="[161,1417,544,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-158@8.[151,1436,525,1892]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Hypoxys crassimarginatum sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777068" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777068/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">Figs. 4D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1118,1153,1954,1981]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[237,1347,191,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-23@10.[219,1367,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Hypoxys cristatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777070" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777070/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">5D</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[1218,1358,1954,1980]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flexuosus">
<emphasis box="[1218,1358,1954,1980]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">H. flexuosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a very small bottle-shaped excavation (
<figureCitation box="[513,600,1988,2015]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[229,1360,193,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-23@14.[214,1373,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Hypoxys flexuosus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777076" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777076/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">Fig. 8E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
